docs.lead_paragraph: The value of United States exports of merchandise, including re-exports, to each of the principal foreign countries except five-China,France, Greece, Japan and the Union of South Africa-increased in October, compared with the same month a year ago, the Department of Commerce reported today in a survey of exports and imports by countries.

docs.lead_paragraph: Federal Judge W. Calvin Chesnut, presiding at the trial of fourteen seamen charged with mutiny on the government-owned freighter Algic, charged the jury today that legally "there is no right to strike against the laws of the United States at any time, any place or under any conditions."
